description:
The incidence of cancer is staggering. Nearly 1 in 2 people will face this dreaded disease in their lifetime. What are cancer risk factors and how can you avoid them? If cancer runs in your family, will you inherit it? Or is it possible, by lifestyle choices, to prevent even an inherited tendency for cancer development?

Dr. Diane Burnett discusses what cancer is, what causes it, and how to prevent it. Did you know that everyday every one of us is producing cancer cells? The good news is research has shown there is much we can do to prevent the development of cancer. Learn about the single most important factor in preventing cancer. Discover the role of antioxidants in cancer prevention and top sources for antioxidants. Today is the day to put preventive measures into practice. 


For more, please visit our website: https://amazingdiscoveries.org
